text: West Pinjarra is a suburb of the town of Pinjarra in the Peel Region of Western Australia. Its local government area is the Shire of Murray. It is a predominantly industrial suburb, with many engineering and manufacturing facilities located there. It is connected to other parts of WA by the Forrest Highway and Pinjarra Road. ==References== Category:Towns in Western Australia Category:Shire of Murray
title: West Pinjarra, Western Australia
